3.01	Brad_Lamm	Brad Lamm	Brad Lamm is an American interventionist, educator, and author of How to Change Someone You Love: Four Steps to Help You Help Them (2009), which details the theory and practice of a system of psychosocial intervention he designed and named "Lifestyle Intervention” which trains, and then utilizes, the friends and family of the addict as an ongoing support group or “circle of change.” Lamm is also the author of Just 10 Lbs: Easy Steps to Weighing What You Want (Finally) (2011), a self-help book on dieting and compulsive overeating.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/BradLamm.2011B.jpeg/220px-BradLamm.2011B.jpeg
